{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To address this challenge, Wei et al. (2021) proposed a novel approach called edge-enhanced Bayesian graph convolutional network (EBGCN) for rumor detection.",
    "This model addresses the uncertainty issue in the propagation structure by modeling it from a probability perspective.",
    "Similar to BiGCN (Bian et al. 2020), for each news event, two weighted propagation graphs (topdown and bottom-up) are constructed.",
    "The feature vector of each node is then extracted using the TF-IDF method.",
    "These two propagation graphs are processed separately by two GCNs."
  ],
